---
description: Never commit, push, or do any git write operation without explicit user instruction
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git discipline

NEVER run any of these without the user explicitly saying "commit", "push", "запушь", "сделай коммит", or similar direct instruction:

- `git commit`
- `git push`
- `git pull` (write side)
- `git branch -D`
- `git rebase`
- `git merge`
- `gh pr create`

This applies even when work is "done" and "ready". Wait for explicit instruction every time.

Stage files only when the user has already confirmed to commit. Never use `git add .` or `git add -A` — stage by filename only.
